\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Add\">Add</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/ChartedSpace.html#ChartedSpace\">ChartedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">H</span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_extends\">extends</span> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/IsManifold/Basic.html#IsManifold\">IsManifold</a> <span class=\"fn\">I</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Basic hypothesis to talk about a `C^n` (Lie) additive monoid or a `C^n` additive\nsemigroup. A `C^n` additive monoid over `G`, for example, is obtained by requiring both the\ninstances `AddMonoid G` and `ContMDiffAdd I n G`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/Algebra/Monoid.html#ContMDiffAdd","kind":"class","line":44,"name":"ContMDiffAdd","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/Algebra/Monoid.lean#L44-L52"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/Algebra/Monoid.html#LibraryNote.Design_choices_about_smooth_algebraic_structures\"><span class=\"name\">LibraryNote</span>.<span class=\"name\">Design_choices_about_smooth_algebraic_structures</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Util/LibraryNote.html#Batteries.Util.LibraryNote\">Batteries.Util.LibraryNote</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"1. All `C^n` algebraic structures on `G` are `Prop`-valued classes that extend\n`IsManifold I n G`. This way we save users from adding both\n`[IsManifold I n G]` and `[ContMDiffMul I n G]` to the assumptions. While many API\nlemmas hold true without the `IsManifold I n G` assumption, we're not aware of a\nmathematically interesting monoid on a topological manifold such that (a) the space is not a\n`IsManifold`; (b) the multiplication is `C^n` at `(a, b)` in the charts\n`extChartAt I a`, `extChartAt I b`, `extChartAt I (a * b)`.\n\n2. Because of `ModelProd` we can't assume, e.g., that a `LieGroup` is modelled on `𝓘(𝕜, E)`. So,\nwe formulate the definitions and lemmas for any model.\n\n3. While smoothness of an operation implies its continuity, lemmas like\n`continuousMul_of_contMDiffMul` can't be instances because otherwise Lean would have to search for\n`ContMDiffMul I n G` with unknown `𝕜`, `E`, `H`, and `I : ModelWithCorners 𝕜 E H`. If users needs\n`[ContinuousMul G]` in a proof about a `C^n` monoid, then they need to either add\n`[ContinuousMul G]` as an assumption (worse) or use `haveI` in the proof (better). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/Algebra/Monoid.html#LibraryNote.Design_choices_about_smooth_algebraic_structures","kind":"def","line":25,"name":"LibraryNote.Design_choices_about_smooth_algebraic_structures","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/Algebra/Monoid.lean#L25-L41"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Geometry.Manifold.ContMDiffMap","Mathlib.Geometry.Manifold.MFDeriv.Basic"],"instances":[{"className":"ContMDiffMul","name":"instContMDiffMulOfSomeENatTopOfLEInfty","typeNames":[]},{"className":"ContMDiffAdd","name":"instContMDiffAddOfSomeENatTopOfLEInfty","typeNames":[]},{"className":"ContMDiffMul","name":"instContMDiffMulOfTopWithTopENat","typeNames":[]},{"className":"ContMDiffAdd","name":"instContMDiffAddOfTopWithTopENat","typeNames":[]},{"className":"ContMDiffMul","name":"instContMDiffMulOfNatWithTopENatOfContinuousMul","typeNames":["OfNat.ofNat"]},{"className":"ContMDiffAdd","name":"instContMDiffAddOfNatWithTopENatOfContinuousAdd","typeNames":["OfNat.ofNat"]},{"className":"ContMDiffMul","name":"instContMDiffMulOfNatWithTopENat","typeNames":["OfNat.ofNat"]},{"className":"ContMDiffAdd","name":"instContMDiffAddOfNatWithTopENat","typeNames":["OfNat.ofNat"]},{"className":"ContMDiffMul","name":"ContMDiffMul.prod","typeNames":["ModelWithCorners.prod","Prod"]},{"className":"ContMDiffAdd","name":"ContMDiffAdd.prod","typeNames":["ModelWithCorners.prod","Prod"]},{"className":"One","name":"instOneContMDiffMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"Zero","name":"instZeroContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"Inhabited","name":"instInhabitedContMDiffMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"Inhabited","name":"instInhabitedContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"DFunLike","name":"instFunLikeContMDiffMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"DFunLike","name":"instFunLikeContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"MonoidHomClass","name":"instMonoidHomClassContMDiffMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"AddMonoidHomClass","name":"instAddMonoidHomClassContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"ContinuousMapClass","name":"instContinuousMapClassContMDiffMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"ContinuousMapClass","name":"instContinuousMapClassContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism","typeNames":["ContMDiffAddMonoidMorphism"]},{"className":"ContMDiffAdd","name":"instContMDiffAddSelf","typeNames":["modelWithCornersSelf"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Geometry.Manifold.Algebra.Monoid"}